\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. B. elongata} Ehrh.,{\i  Beitr. Naturk. }{\b 7}: 159 (1792). Biennial or short-lived perennial. Lower leaves petiolate, obovate to elliptical, sinuate-pinnatifid or entire, covered with curved bristles on both surfaces. Petals 7-10 mm, yellow. Siliqua 15-22 mm, attenuate into a seedless beak 0·5-2·5 mm, with gynophore 1·5-4·5 mm.{\i  S.E. & E.C. Europe; naturalized elsewhere as a weed or ruderal.} Au Bu Cz Hu Ju *Po Rm Rs(W, K, E) [Da Ga Ge Ho It Rs(C)].
