\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. B. nivalis} Boiss. & Heldr. in Boiss., {\i Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  3}({\b 1}): 32 (1856) ({\i Brassicella nivalis} (Boiss. & Heldr.) O.E. Schulz, {\i Rhynchosinapis nivalis} (Boiss. & Heldr.) Heywood, {\i Hutera nivalis} (Boiss. & Heldr.) Gómez-Campo, {\i Coincya nivalis }(Boiss. & Heldr.) Greuter & Burdet). Glabrous or subglabrous, caespitose perennial, somewhat woody at the base; stems 10-50 cm, usually unbranched. Cauline leaves few, small, linear, often absent. Sepals 4-5 mm, obtuse; petals 8-11 mm, yellow. Pedicels erecto-patent. Siliqua 25-60 × 1·5-2 mm, somewhat curved, constricted between the seeds; beak 1-3 mm, without seeds. Seeds 10-18 mm.{\i  Limestone scree, usually above} 1800{\i  m. N. Greece; S.W. Bulgaria; local}. Bu Gr.
