\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. B. macrocarpa} Guss., {\i Ind. Sem. Horto Boccad.}{\b  1824/5}: 3 (1825). Glabrous small shrub; stems 30-60 cm. Basal leaves 10-18 × 4-10 cm, lyrate-pinnatifid or pinnatilobed, the lobes crenate-dentate, petioles up to 8 cm; cauline leaves oblong to lanceolate, entire or shallowly toothed. Petals 10-15 mm, yellow. Siliqua 20-40 × 5-12 mm, -very thick and fleshy; valves thick and woody, 1-veined, boat-shaped, attenuate into a conical, 0- to 2-seeded beak 8-13 mm.{\i  Maritime rocks. • W. Sicilia }({\i Isole Egadi}). Si.
